     {q:"Each body paragraph in a research essay should begin with ___.", options:["a quotation","a topic sentence that states the paragraph's main point","a new thesis","a conclusion"], answer:1},
     {q:"In-text citations or references are used to ___.", options:["make the essay longer","give credit to sources and allow readers to verify information","only in long essays","avoid using evidence"], answer:1},
     {q:"The conclusion of a research essay should ___.", options:["introduce new evidence","repeat the introduction word for word","synthesise the key findings, restate the thesis, and explain the broader significance","be only one sentence"], answer:2},
     {q:"Why is it important to paraphrase rather than copy sources?", options:["It is not","To avoid plagiarism and to demonstrate your own understanding of the material","Only for professional writers","Only in exams"], answer:1}
